SIMPLE: acquittance
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acquittance
<hw>Ac*quit"tance</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>aquitance</ets>, fr. <ets>aquiter</ets>. See
<er>Acquit</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The clearing off of debt or
obligation; a release or discharge from debt or other
liability.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A writing which is evidence of a discharge; a
receipt in full, which bars a further demand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You can produce <qex>acquittances</qex>⟦br⟧
For such a sum, from special officers.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acquittance</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Acquittance
<hw>Ac*quit"tance</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To acquit.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acquitter</ent>⟦br⟧
